Installing pyS5p
================

Building from source
--------------------

The latest release of pyS5p is available from:
https://github.com/rmvanhees/pys5p

Once you have satisfied the requirements detailed below, simply run::

python setup.py install

Requirements
~~~~~~~~~~~~
These external packages are required to install pyS5p or gain access to
significant pyS5p functionality.

It is adviced to use pip to install the Python packages and to use the latest
versions of the software libraries. However, many of these packages are also
available in Linux package managers such as aptitude and yum.

**python** 3.5 or later (https://www.python.org/)
    pyS5p requires Python 3.5 or later.

**Cython** 0.25 or later (https://pypi.python.org/pypi/Cython/)

**numpy** 1.11 or later (http://www.numpy.org/)
    Python package for scientific computing including a powerful N-dimensional
    array object.

**h5py** 2.6  or later (www.h5py.org/)
    HDF5 for Python

**matplotlib** 1.5.x or later (http://matplotlib.org/)
    Python package for 2D plotting.  This package is required for any
    graphical capability.

**GEOS** 3.3.3 or later (https://trac.osgeo.org/geos/)
    GEOS is an API of spatial predicates and functions for processing geometry
    written in C++.

**PROJ.4** 4.9.0 or later (https://trac.osgeo.org/proj/)
    Cartographic Projections library.

**PROJ.4** 4.9.0 or later (https://trac.osgeo.org/proj/)
    Cartographic Projections library.

Testing Dependencies
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
These packages are required for the full pyS5p test suite to run.

**nose** 1.2.1 or later (https://nose.readthedocs.org/en/latest/)
    Python package for software testing.

